CD133+ population from Colo205 is enriched in ALDH1-positive cells

We investigated the presence of the ALDH1 marker on Colo205 cells after CD133 selection.

Quantification was then performed by cytometry analyses.
('Quantification', 'was performed by', 'cytometry analyses')

The results revealed that 1.7±0.2% of CD133+ cells co-expressed the ALDH1 molecule, while 0.2±0.1% of CD133- cells did.

The Colo205 CD133+ cell population was thus shown to be enriched in terms of ALDH1-expressing cells.

CD133+ subpopulation displays increased invasiveness.
('CD133 displays', 'increased', 'invasiveness')

In vitro invasion assays were performed on several Colo205 sorted subpopulations using a collagen-based cell invasion method.
('invasion assays', 'were performed on', 'Colo205')

The results showed that the CD133+ purified population was significantly more invasive than the CD133- resulting fraction or the control fraction (absorbance units (AU)=0.99, 0.15 and 0.27, respectively; P&lt;0.01).

No significant difference was observed for both CD44+ and CD44- fractions (AU=0.30 and 0.26, respectively) (Figure ).
('No difference', 'was observed for', 'CD44')

These results confirmed that Colo205 CD133+ cells exhibited greater tumorigenic capacity than the CD133- and CD44+/− cells.

