Colo205 CD133+ cells have specific metabolome expression

To identify specific metabolome features, CE-TOF-MS analyses were performed after cell sorting.
('analyses', 'were performed after', 'cell sorting')

The results showed that only the CD133+ purified fraction had a significantly different metabolome profile compared with the other cell fractions.

No significant difference was observed for CD44+, CD44-, CD133- and parental Colo205 cells (Figure ).
('No difference', 'was observed for', 'CD44')

On the one hand, the CD133+ cell fraction exhibited high overall increases in glycogen, components of the citrate cycle, nucleotides and components of co-factor metabolism pathways (from two to ten times higher than in parental Colo205 cells).
