('data acquisition', 'were processed using', 'Agilent Chemstation software')

CE-TOF-MS was conducted in both positive and negative ion modes for each sample.

Molecule separation was processed in fused-silica capillaries filled with 1 M formic acid as a background electrolyte.
('Molecule separation', 'was processed in', 'capillaries filled with M acid')

Samples were injected at 50 mbar, and a voltage of 27 kV (for cation mode) or 30 kV (for anion mode) was applied.
