Capillary temperature was maintained at 20°C while sample tray temperature was kept below 10°C.
('Capillary temperature', 'was maintained at', 'C')
('sample tray temperature', 'was kept below', 'C.')

Sheath liquid was delivered at 10 μL/min.
('Sheath liquid', 'was delivered at', 'mL')

Capillary voltage was set at 4 kV for cation mode and 3.5 kV for anion mode; the flow rate of nitrogen gas (heater temperature 300°C) was set at 0.35 bar.
('voltage', 'was set at', 'kV')
('flow rate of nitrogen gas', 'was set at', 'bar')

Fragmentor, skimmer and Oct RFV voltages were set according to HMT setting recommendations (HMT Inc.).
('Fragmentor', 'were set according', 'to')
('skimmer', 'were set according', 'to')
('Oct RFV voltages', 'were set according', 'to')

Exact mass data were acquired at a rate of 1.5 cycles per second over the range of 50–1000 m/z.
